  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta) and cook over a high heat for 15-20 min or until tender</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain (in a sieve so you don't lose it!) and leave to steam dry&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim the green stalks off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and chop into large, bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Deseed the <strong>yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cut into wedges&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine</strong>, <strong>yellow pepper strips</strong> and <strong>red onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray and drizzle generously with <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until everything is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>capers</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 2-3 min until starting to bubble&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/988.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
